{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778554405,"nonce":"I2fSNJ8G/y1NQhEUyzInQimqlis=","title":"MVP: linear regulator vs tracker decoupling acid test (laptop-CPU)","message":"MVP-scoped child of `d448c9d`. Implements the minimal version of the decoupling acid test so we can get a first signal on the regulator-vs-tracker hypothesis without cloud compute or new feedbax architecture.\n\n## Scope\n\nTwo architectures (skip the affine recurrent and GRU variants from `d448c9d` for now):\n\n1. **`LinearController`**: `u_t = -K_t ┬Ę x_t` with K_t a learned LTV gain of shape `(T ├Ś 2 ├Ś 4)` Ōēł 1,120 params.\n2. **`LinearTrackerController`**: `u_t = u_ff(t) - K_t ┬Ę (x_t - x_nom(t))` with K_t and u_ff(t) both learned LTV, Ōēł 1,400 params total. Use a raw time-indexed parameter vector for u_ff(t), not an MLP.\n\nBoth implement feedbaxs `Component` interface (`__call__(inputs, state, *, key) ŌåÆ (outputs_dict, state)`, `input_ports = (\"input\", \"feedback\")`, `output_ports = (\"output\", \"hidden\")`, with a `NetworkState`-bearing `StateIndex`). They live in rlrmp, not feedbax ŌĆö no feedbax changes required if time is threaded as a task input channel via `task.add_input(name=\"time\", ...)`.\n\n## Training plan\n\n- Local CPU on Apple Silicon (no cloud)\n- Warmup-only training (no adversary phase for the MVP ŌĆö the discriminator test is on the standard-trained ╬öv signature)\n- ~1000 batches at batch_size 64 should suffice for these tiny models; expected wall time 1ŌĆō4 min after JIT (~10ŌĆō30 s)\n- Use the same task and plant config as the f47abb1 winner (post-go powerlaw, no jerk) for direct comparison\n\n## Implementation touchpoints\n\n- New: `src/rlrmp/networks/linear_controllers.py` (or similar) ŌĆö both controllers\n- Modified: `scripts/train_minimax.py` `_get_trainable` (~5 lines) to handle the new controller parameter structure\n- Modified: maybe `scripts/train_minimax.py` model-construction path to allow `--hidden-type linear` / `linear_tracker`\n- Loss: set `nn_hidden=0` (semantics dont match for linear controllers); keep position/velocity losses\n\n## Discriminator prediction (from `d448c9d`)\n\n- Regulator ŌåÆ ╬öv \u003e 0 (consistent with linear-controller-inflates-velocity claim)\n- Tracker ŌåÆ ╬öv Ōēł 0 (decoupling via separately learned feedforward channel)\n\nIf regulator and tracker split sign cleanly on ╬öv, the decoupling-via-parameterisation explanation is the best fit. If both give similar ╬öv, decoupling-via-parameterisation is not the mechanism.\n\n## Out of scope (future work, still on `d448c9d` / `f695729`)\n\n- Affine recurrent controller (variant 3)\n- GRU baseline (variant 4) ŌĆö we already have GRU results from f47abb1\n- Full-state ╬Ą adversary (depends on `d448c9d`s \"issue TBD\" adversary class)\n- PGD inner-step sweep\n\n## Cross-refs\n\n- Parent: `d448c9d` (full-scope acid test)\n- Umbrella: `f695729` (regulator-coupling and biomechanical decoupling)","files":null}]}